        <div class="pub-details">
          <div class="pub-details-inner">
            <div class="pub-venue">Outlet: UNU-WIDER, 2026</div>
            <div class="pub-description">The SOUTHMOD modelling conventions, based on the EUROMOD conventions and adapted for developing-country settings through the work of UNU-WIDER, ISER, SASPRI, and national teams. They guide how to build a model and keep it up to date, and standardize data and modelling choices across the countries in the project. The document is shared publicly for researchers building their own models on the free EUROMOD/SOUTHMOD software. Careful, systematic checking of the input data and all model elements is essential, and it remains the user's responsibility to judge how comparable the models are for a given research question. The relevant Country Report and Data Requirement Document are worth reading, and UNU-WIDER can provide the Stata do-files behind the data on request.</div>
